    "causal_summary": "The `external/` folder of this packet contains the public Xanther Context Engine (XCE) integration repository — README, MIT license, MCP configs for 5 IDEs, and 3 steering files (`CLAUDE.md`, `kiro.md`, `opencode-prompt.txt`). XCE is a hosted SaaS MCP server that delivers architectural context (HLD, LLD, component descriptions, call graphs, impact analysis) via 5 tool primitives, claiming +7.4pp on SWE-bench Verified for Sonnet 4.0 and ~20% token reduction when steering rules are active. The underlying PRAT (Persistent Recursive Abstract Tree) algorithm is closed-source. Pt-01 produced the original 5 code-graph + skill-advisor phases. Pt-02 cross-validated and surfaced 6 open code-graph policy decisions. Pt-03 (2026-05-09, gpt-5.5 high fast, 10 iter) extended scope to mcp-coco-index and the system-spec-kit memory backend / causal graph — 56 file:line-cited findings producing a bounded-ADAPT verdict matrix across RQ-A1..A5 (coco) + RQ-B1..B5 (memory). 5 additional L3 phase scaffolds shipped 2026-05-09T11:30Z: 006 coco intent steering (L3, ~250-350 LOC), 007 memory semantic triggers (L3, ~280-430 LOC), 008 feedback reducers + 3 P0 fixes (L3, ~400-650 LOC), 009 retrieval rerank clients (L3, ~250-420 LOC), 010 coco+memory context extras (L3, ~500-800 LOC). Each new packet has 9 files including per-child resource-map per user directive. Every recommendation default-off / shadow-first / fail-closed / Phase-005 eval gated. Critical P0 guard fixes inside Phase 008 Sub-Phase 1: (i) auto-provenance cap broadening for RQ-B3 reducer; (ii) manual-edge overwrite guard; (iii) constitutional/critical retention basement gap in memory-retention-sweep. Total 10 phase children now scaffolded.",
